channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump shooting suspect visited gun range dozens of times, including holidays: Senator
item.description: The suspect in the assassination attempt against former President Donald Trump visited a gun club dozens of times, according to records released by Sen. Chuck Grassley.

item.title: My Mom's Support For Trump Divided Our Family. Then I Found The Crack In Her MAGA Armor.
Man found dead hours after being questioned about girl's 1996 murder
item.description: Nearly three decades after 15-year-old Danielle Houchins was found dead, authorities say DNA finally led them to her killer.

item.title: Athlete drowns during CrossFit Games in Texas
item.description: An athlete drowned during a swimming event at a CrossFit competition in Texas on Thursday, the organization said.

item.title: Trump said he ‘went down’ in helicopter ‘emergency landing’ with former San Francisco mayor, who says it never happened
Chi Chi Rodriguez, Hall of Fame golfer and "showman," dies at 88
item.description: The PGA called Chi Chi Rodriguez "a showman on the course, a tireless philanthropist off the course."

item.title: Noah Lyles' Olympics drama prompts concern over Paris COVID spread
item.description: Noah Lyles’ characteristically exuberant walkout for Thursday’s 200-meter final gave little indication that he was among the dozens of Olympians suffering from COVID-19.

item.title: TCSO updates community on dog involved in camper assault
Travis Scott detained in Paris after fight at hotel, prosecutors say
item.description: Rapper Travis Scott was detained at a Paris hotel after an altercation with a security guard, French prosecutors say.

item.title: 15-year-old American loses leg in Belize shark attack
item.description: An American teenager has lost a leg to a shark attack while vacationing in Central America.

item.title: California lawmaker switches party, criticizes Democratic leadership
Harris, Biden to campaign together for first time since he dropped out of race
item.description: Vice President Harris and President Biden will make their first joint campaign trip next week since he dropped out of the 2024 presidential race, the White House says. They'll head to Maryland.

item.title: 3rd teenager arrested in foiled attack on Taylor Swift concerts in Vienna, Austria
item.description: Austrian Interior Minister Gerhard Karner said a third teenager has been arrested in connection with the foiled attack on now-canceled Taylor Swift concerts in Vienna.

item.title: SLO police identify suspect, seize car in deadly hit-and-run crash
Jan. 6 rioter stormed Capitol with her sword and whip, FBI says
item.description: Kennedy Lindsey was arrested in Los Angeles on charges including disorderly conduct and possession of a dangerous weapon.
